{"action": "input", "code": "def get_pattern_color(input_grid: np.ndarray, pattern: np.ndarray) -> int:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given an input grid and a pattern, returns the color which appears in each cell of the pattern.\n    \"\"\"\n    color_counts = {}\n    for i in range(pattern.shape[0]):\n        for j in range(pattern.shape[1]):\n            if pattern[i][j] != -1:\n                color = input_grid[i][j]\n                if color in color_counts:\n                    color_counts[color] += 1\n                else:\n                    color_counts[color] = 1\n    return max(color_counts, key=color_counts.get)\ndef is_not_indicator_pattern(pattern: np.ndarray, indicator_pattern: np.ndarray) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given a pattern and an indicator pattern, returns True if the pattern is not the indicator pattern, False otherwise.\n    \"\"\"\n    return not np.array_equal(pattern, indicator_pattern)\ndef get_other_color(pattern: np.ndarray, indicator_color: int) -> int:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given a pattern and an indicator color, returns the other color of this pattern which is not the indicator color.\n    \"\"\"\n    unique_colors = np.unique(pattern)\n    for color in unique_colors:\n        if color != indicator_color:\n            return color\n    return -1\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    patterns = get_continuous_patterns(input_grid)\n    output_grid = input_grid\n    indicator_color = get_pattern_color(input_grid, patterns)\n    indicator_pattern = find_pattern_with_two_colors(input_grid, patterns)\n    for pattern in patterns:\n        if is_not_indicator_pattern(pattern, indicator_pattern):\n            color_use = get_other_color(input_grid, pattern, indicator_color)\n            output_grid = scale_up_pattern(output_grid, pattern, indicator_pattern, color, indicator_color)\n    return output_grid\ndef get_continuous_patterns(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> List[np.ndarray]:\n    patterns = []\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[0]):\n        for j in range(input_grid.shape[1]):\n            if input_grid[i][j] != -1:\n                pattern = _get_continuous_pattern(input_grid, i, j)\n                patterns.append(pattern)\n    return patterns\ndef find_pattern_with_two_colors(patterns: List[np.ndarray]) -> Optional[np.ndarray]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given a list of patterns, returns the pattern which contains different numbers of pixels of two colors.\n    If no such pattern exists, returns None.\n    \"\"\"\n    for pattern in patterns:\n        unique_colors = np.unique(pattern)\n        if len(unique_colors) == 2:\n            color_counts = np.bincount(pattern.flatten())\n            if len(color_counts[color_counts != 0]) == 2:\n                return pattern\n    return None\ndef scale_up_pattern(input_grid: np.ndarray, pattern: np.ndarray, indicator_pattern: np.ndarray, color_use: int, indicator_color: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Changes black pixels near the given pattern to color_use to enlarge the pattern, so that the pattern becomes a scaled up version of the indicator_pattern.\n    \"\"\"\n    output_grid = input_grid.copy()\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[0]):\n        for j in range(input_grid.shape[1]):\n            if pattern[i][j] == black:\n                for x in range(-1, 2):\n                    for y in range(-1, 2):\n                        if i + x >= 0 and i + x < input_grid.shape[0] and (j + y >= 0) and (j + y < input_grid.shape[1]):\n                            if indicator_pattern[x][y] != black and input_grid[i + x][j + y] == indicator_color:\n                                output_grid[i + x][j + y] = color_use\n    return output_grid", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n  patterns = `get all continuous patterns`(input_grid)\n  output_grid = input_grid\n  indicator_color = `the color which appears in each pattern`(input_grid, patterns)\n  indicator_pattern = `find the pattern which contain different numbers of pixels of two c